# {{DOMAIN_NAME}} Wiki

Private second-brain on **{{DOMAIN_NAME}}**{{DOMAIN_ONE_LINER}}. Built on **Karpathy's
"LLM Wiki"** idea — synthesis happens once at ingest time, into a persistent, compounding
graph of cross-linked, cited markdown pages (not RAG-at-query-time). It is a knowledge
artifact **for the human**, used to understand the problem space before building.

This wiki is its own git repository and lives **outside** any app codebase.

## How it works

Drop raw material in → run `/ingest` → Claude Code synthesizes wiki pages with
cross-links and citations. Ask questions with `/query`. Periodically run `/lint` to keep
the graph clean.

## Layout

- `raw/` — immutable source material (articles, references, transcripts, podcast notes,
  tweets, gists, repo notes). **Never edited by hand or by the LLM.**
- `wiki/` — LLM-generated synthesis: concepts, entities, workflows, source summaries,
  indexes. Browse from [`wiki/MOC.md`](wiki/MOC.md).
- `_meta/` — ingest log + lint reports.
- `.claude/commands/` — slash command definitions.
- `CLAUDE.md` — full conventions (read this if you're hacking on the wiki structure itself).

## Adding new material

**Local file** — drop it into the right `raw/` subfolder, then:

```
/ingest raw/articles/some-source.md
```

**URL** — skip the manual save:

```
/ingest https://example.com/some-article
```

`/ingest` proposes a plan first (N new pages, M updates, K cross-links). Approve, or pass
`--yolo` to skip approval.

## Asking questions

```
/query "what are the core trade-offs in <topic>?"
```

Answers cite `[[wiki-slug]]` for every claim. If a claim can't be cited, the answer says
so and names a source to ingest. If the answer synthesizes across multiple pages,
`/query` offers to promote it to `wiki/inbox/` as a draft page — confirm in a follow-up
turn to save it.

## Maintenance

```
/lint            # report only
/lint --fix      # apply safe fixes (broken-link renames, frontmatter normalization, trivial backlinks)
```

Reports land in `_meta/lint-reports/<timestamp>.md`. Contradictions and suggested new
pages are surfaced as suggestions, never auto-applied.

## Open in Obsidian (optional)

Point Obsidian at this folder ("Open folder as vault"). Recommended core plugins:
Backlinks, Outgoing Links, Graph View, Tags View, Properties, Search. Suggested settings:
new-note location → `wiki/inbox/`; new link format → "Shortest path when possible"; Use
Wikilinks → on.

## Credit

The pattern is Andrej Karpathy's "LLM Wiki." This vault ships a hardened implementation
of it (citation discipline, plan-before-write, layered `raw/ → wiki/ → _meta/`, query
reads synthesis only).
